<TITLE> Budget for women </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com) This year's budget makes provisions for women of various economic strata, from tax breaks for working women to incentives for women entrepreneurs and widening of the social safety net for disadvantaged women. The budget proposes raising the tax-free income ceiling by Tk 15,000 to Tk 165,000 for women tax-payers and those aged over 70, whereas the existing limit for tax-free income of Tk 150,000 will remain uncharged for men under 70. To encourage women entrepreneurs, the new National Women Entrepreneurs Forum will begin a credit operation at low rates of interest, financed by the Small and Medium Enterprise Endowment Fund which has been doubled to Tk 200 crore in this year's proposed budget. SME exporters of handicrafts will enjoy tax-free income from July 1, 2008, to June 30, 2011, the annual turnover limit for 'cottage industries' will be raised to Tk 2,400,000 from Tk 2,000,000, VAT will be withdrawn from the production stage of handmade biscuits and handloom fabricsall these measures should provide impetus to women friendly industries. For widowed, deserted and destitute women, the next budget aims to raise the rate of allowances from Tk 220 to Tk 250 per person, and increase beneficiary coverage for the allowances from 8,25,000 to 9,00,000 women, This will result in an allocation of Tk 270 crore, Tk 86 crore higher than the revised allocation for the current fiscal year, finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said in his budget speech. The government launched a pilot programme titled allowance for poor lactating mothers in the fiscal year just ending, under which the number of beneficiaries will be increased from the existing 45,000 to 60,000. "The idea of introducing this assistance has been widely acclaimed," the finance adviser said. The allocation in the next fiscal year will be Tk 21.60 crore for the programme, 27 percent higher than the current year's allocation.
